[SPEAKER_03]: I just, just something that David said about, you know, randomized, you know, once, once you really start targeting a particular group.

1073
01:36:11,045 --> 01:36:20,388
[SPEAKER_03]: you're kind of losing that, you know, that valuable piece of a survey that it's, you know, randomized to the general public.

1074
01:36:20,708 --> 01:36:24,269
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, that's something just to consider.

1075
01:36:24,389 --> 01:36:36,273
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, should we just like keep blasting it and, you know, have a goal of having 600 people to have a big sample size of randomized people would make sense.

1076
01:36:37,349 --> 01:36:39,270
[SPEAKER_03]: That's just my initial thought.

1077
01:36:39,490 --> 01:36:42,451
[SPEAKER_03]: But to say, well, we're going to go get renters.

1078
01:36:42,491 --> 01:36:44,893
[SPEAKER_03]: And then we're going to get 300 renters.

1079
01:36:44,993 --> 01:36:55,097
[SPEAKER_03]: And then now we're going to kind of skew the results, that this is a renters survey.

1080
01:36:55,958 --> 01:36:57,358
[SPEAKER_03]: Just something to think about.

1081
01:36:58,259 --> 01:36:59,419
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah, no, I agree.

1082
01:36:59,779 --> 01:37:00,180
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

1083
01:37:01,220 --> 01:37:02,200
[SPEAKER_07]: David, and then Eunice.

1084
01:37:04,902 --> 01:37:05,182
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah.

1085
01:37:06,326 --> 01:37:08,788
[SPEAKER_02]: In a similar vein, I'm at Tufts.

1086
01:37:08,928 --> 01:37:14,512
[SPEAKER_02]: I imagine I could start reaching out to the majority of Tufts students or renters who are not living on campus.

1087
01:37:15,833 --> 01:37:25,381
[SPEAKER_02]: That being said, I don't know that that is necessarily, that may or may not be the group we really want to be hearing from.

1088
01:37:26,541 --> 01:37:32,526
[SPEAKER_02]: Tufts students as a whole, from what I know of them, are fairly unaware of Medford politics.

1089
01:37:34,501 --> 01:37:50,132
[SPEAKER_02]: I talk to them all the time about the stuff that's going on in Medford politics, and I've never met a Medford student who can name Medford's mayor or anything like that, which, you know, may or may not mean we want to discount kind of their thoughts and opinions on the matter.

1090
01:37:52,633 --> 01:37:55,175
[SPEAKER_02]: But yeah.

1091
01:37:55,255 --> 01:37:56,196
[SPEAKER_05]: Okay, thank you.

1092
01:37:56,536 --> 01:37:56,816
[SPEAKER_05]: Eunice?

1093
01:37:57,717 --> 01:37:59,077
[SPEAKER_05]: I think we need to be following

1094
01:38:00,435 --> 01:38:09,537
[SPEAKER_05]: couple of different tracks here, the usage of social media and electronic, and then the good old fashioned paper copy.

1095
01:38:10,658 --> 01:38:22,721
[SPEAKER_05]: I think, you know, we need to be each personally pushing it, you know, through our own Medford groups that we belong to, the ones that at least allow political stuff, not all of them do.

1096
01:38:25,122 --> 01:38:28,603
[SPEAKER_05]: Along with, you know, just to our own feed, and

1097
01:38:30,263 --> 01:38:33,545
[SPEAKER_05]: you know, getting it out there to our Medford friends.

1098
01:38:36,447 --> 01:38:59,743
[SPEAKER_05]: I think going to some of the, you know, city leaders and specialized groups, the sports teams that we have, the churches, the houses of worship, anywhere that, you know, the chamber, the Medford Family Network, the Medford Mustangs, anywhere and anything

1099
01:39:00,577 --> 01:39:06,301
[SPEAKER_05]: where they can disseminate it to the people in their orbit.

1100
01:39:07,402 --> 01:39:28,438
[SPEAKER_05]: And then I think to go the paper route, I think we need to be photocopying and leaving them at the library, leaving them at the senior center, leaving them in the front hall at city hall, at all of the local schools, anywhere

1101
01:39:29,541 --> 01:39:52,909
[SPEAKER_05]: anywhere that the public might go that, you know, the people that are there would welcome having a survey there and they can fill it out and, you know, mail it back to city hall, drop it off at city hall, you know, or something, you know, deferring of course to David and others who, you know, do this more for a living.

1102
01:39:54,430 --> 01:39:55,270
[SPEAKER_05]: I'm not sure

1103
01:39:56,346 --> 01:40:03,591
[SPEAKER_05]: you know, we have 60 some odd thousand people in the city and, you know, 40,000 registered voters.

1104
01:40:05,052 --> 01:40:14,518
[SPEAKER_05]: I'm not quite sure how, and maybe correct me if I'm wrong, if I'm misunderstanding that 300 or 600 responses is very good.

1105
01:40:14,538 --> 01:40:17,920
[SPEAKER_05]: I would think we would need a heap more of that.

1106
01:40:19,321 --> 01:40:23,864
[SPEAKER_05]: So I don't quite understand how, you know,

1107
01:40:24,699 --> 01:40:29,944
[SPEAKER_05]: a city of 60,000 people and 40,000 registered voters at 600 is good.

1108
01:40:31,706 --> 01:40:38,172
[SPEAKER_07]: Well, we can maybe, I'm sure David can tell us, but I'm just getting a little worried about time right now.

1109
01:40:38,252 --> 01:40:42,115
[SPEAKER_07]: So I think those are great ideas, Eunice.

1110
01:40:42,596 --> 01:40:46,619
[SPEAKER_07]: The issue is that we have, the survey closes on December 1st.

1111
01:40:46,820 --> 01:40:49,182
[SPEAKER_07]: So that's the amount of time we have to push it out.

1112
01:40:49,917 --> 01:40:54,702
[SPEAKER_07]: I like the idea of what I was thinking of when we saw that we didn't really get many renters.

1113
01:40:54,722 --> 01:41:06,433
[SPEAKER_07]: I don't know if there's like a renters organization in Medford, but something, you know, just organizations, I think if we can just get the word out to different groups and organizations in the city.

1114
01:41:07,594 --> 01:41:13,159
[SPEAKER_07]: I know Frances was at the West Medford Community Center and she let me know that she had talked about the survey there.

1115
01:41:14,901 --> 01:41:20,446
[SPEAKER_07]: And so that's just what I think we need to try to make happen in the next couple of months.

1116
01:41:20,846 --> 01:41:21,287
[SPEAKER_07]: Danielle?

1117
01:41:22,167 --> 01:41:26,091
[SPEAKER_01]: I think Kit Collins works with a bunch of renter advocacy stuff.

1118
01:41:26,131 --> 01:41:27,292
[SPEAKER_01]: We could maybe ask her to.

1119
01:41:27,812 --> 01:41:28,613
[SPEAKER_07]: That's a good idea.

1120
