[SPEAKER_07]: The farmers market was also, you know, we had a table there.

1197
01:47:28,056 --> 01:47:30,257
[SPEAKER_07]: We talked to, I think, about 35 people.

1198
01:47:30,277 --> 01:47:34,100
[SPEAKER_07]: We made a little bump in the survey after each of these events.

1199
01:47:34,961 --> 01:47:42,569
[SPEAKER_07]: The only other event that we have on our schedule that people talked about doing was the Oktoberfest on September 30th.

1200
01:47:42,689 --> 01:47:48,174
[SPEAKER_07]: But in order to do these events, we need somebody to be at a table.

1201
01:47:48,475 --> 01:47:52,419
[SPEAKER_07]: So does anybody want to be at a table at Oktoberfest?

1202
01:47:52,519 --> 01:47:55,702
[SPEAKER_07]: We already crossed off the Mystic River celebration because we didn't have anybody.

1203
01:47:59,335 --> 01:48:16,788
[SPEAKER_07]: Okay, so Maury might, I know it's Maury's kind of, you know, he's in the, it's a Chamber of Commerce event, so maybe he'll be willing to do it, or we'll find somebody to do it, but as of now, maybe we won't have a table at Oktoberfest.

1204
01:48:18,029 --> 01:48:23,153
[SPEAKER_07]: We do have the October 19th City Hall events, though, and we do have to plan that.

1205
01:48:24,314 --> 01:48:28,057
[SPEAKER_07]: So we have one meeting left before that event,

1206
01:48:29,564 --> 01:48:36,090
[SPEAKER_07]: last time we had a subcommittee that sort of, cause we had, we planned, you know, we planned the whole presentation, et cetera.

1207
