[SPEAKER_07]: So we might need to do that again, Danielle.

1208
01:48:39,633 --> 01:48:47,740
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm just wondering if like nobody could be at some of these events, if there's like, like public health table or some other table that maybe would just put a flyer there.

1209
01:48:48,500 --> 01:48:48,720
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah.

1210
01:48:49,481 --> 01:48:53,845
[SPEAKER_07]: Well, um, I don't know about the mystic river celebration.

1211
01:48:54,145 --> 01:48:54,565
[SPEAKER_07]: I don't know.

1212
01:48:54,585 --> 01:48:57,588
[SPEAKER_07]: I think, I mean, to do that one, we, we would have had to have

1213
01:48:58,033 --> 01:49:02,174
[SPEAKER_07]: paid for a table anyway, and I don't know.

1214
01:49:02,194 --> 01:49:07,395
[SPEAKER_07]: I will ask Laura Brereton about that.

1215
01:49:08,235 --> 01:49:10,656
[SPEAKER_07]: And we can ask Maury about Oktoberfest.

1216
01:49:13,476 --> 01:49:20,238
[SPEAKER_07]: And possibly the thing about the Brazilian flag day, somebody would have to provide the materials.

1217
01:49:20,258 --> 01:49:24,258
[SPEAKER_07]: They might be willing to put them out on a table, but somebody has to provide them.

1218
01:49:24,318 --> 01:49:26,459
[SPEAKER_00]: I think you have to be careful because it was,

1219
01:49:27,702 --> 01:49:31,768
[SPEAKER_00]: Even though I was at the West Medford Community Center, and I made it very clear

1220
01:49:34,295 --> 01:49:36,836
[SPEAKER_00]: that I'm simply sharing information.

1221
01:49:36,856 --> 01:49:48,861
[SPEAKER_00]: A lot of questions came back to me and it was being referred to, I was associated with the city and it was being referred to as the city is changing the charter.

1222
01:49:49,421 --> 01:49:52,863
[SPEAKER_00]: So I just, I think there has to be a clear distinction.

1223
01:49:52,923 --> 01:49:58,045
[SPEAKER_00]: Like if I go to Brazilian Flag Day, I'm going as me for city work.

1224
01:49:58,796 --> 01:49:59,236
[SPEAKER_00]: Right?

1225
01:49:59,877 --> 01:50:08,260
[SPEAKER_00]: And I don't think that there's a problem if the flyers are there, but somebody from the Charter Committee really should be there with those flyers.

1226
01:50:09,821 --> 01:50:10,661
[SPEAKER_07]: Okay, thank you.

1227
01:50:10,681 --> 01:50:15,964
[SPEAKER_00]: Because it can be misinterpreted that it's the city that's pushing this, and it's really not.

1228
01:50:16,324 --> 01:50:23,107
[SPEAKER_00]: We're doing a study so that you can solicit opinion from people within the community.

1229
01:50:24,165 --> 01:50:27,746
[SPEAKER_00]: in order to inform on what the community says.

1230
01:50:28,126 --> 01:50:32,408
[SPEAKER_00]: But the minute there's a city person present, it sort of gets overshadowed.

1231
01:50:34,849 --> 01:50:35,289
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

1232
01:50:35,769 --> 01:50:36,169
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah.

1233
01:50:36,689 --> 01:50:48,314
[SPEAKER_07]: I mean, and people do have a, I mean, just having done this at Circle the Square and the farmers market and people definitely have a lot of questions when they see the materials.

1234
01:50:48,534 --> 01:50:49,454
[SPEAKER_07]: So that's a good point.

1235
01:50:49,514 --> 01:50:50,194
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Frances.

1236
01:50:53,552 --> 01:50:57,938
[SPEAKER_07]: So in terms, we know we are having an event on October 19th at city hall.

1237
01:50:59,400 --> 01:51:05,829
